article.description: — Kobe Rodgers scored 20 points to help Charleston defeat Delaware 90-71 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Rodgers scores 20, Charleston cruises past Delaware 90-71
article.linkText: Rodgers scores 20, Charleston cruises past Delaware 90-71
article.story: NEWARK, Del. -- — Kobe Rodgers scored 20 points to help Charleston defeat Delaware 90-71 on Thursday night. Rodgers added four steals for the Cougars (21-7, 12-3 Coastal Athletic Association), who have won six in a row. James Scott totaled 13 points on 6-for-8 shooting with six rebounds and three blocks. Ben Burnham pitched in with 11 points and seven rebounds. Gerald Drumgoole Jr. led the Fightin' Blue Hens (17-11, 9-6) with 14 points. Jyare Davis added 13 points and Jalun Trent scored 12 points with three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
